    "summary": "I am Emeritus Professor of Functional Linguistics at VU University Amsterdam, now mainly working as a Consultant in Languages and Linguistics, with over 40 years of experience behind me. My skills and expertise are primarily in European languages, with a specialization in English linguistics; I am fluent in several European languages. I take a functionalist approach to language analysis; that is, I am convinced that the structure of languages is adapted to their primary purpose, communication between human beings. I am editor of the world's major journal in functional linguistics, Functions of Language.\n\nI have been associated with three research groups: SCIMITAR, at Santiago de Compostela, Spain; EMO-FUNDETT, at UNED, Spain; and CELGA-ILTEC, at Coimbra, Portugal. I am experienced in research assessment and have worked for several years as an expert -- and in 2012 as lead expert -- for EACEA, an agency of the European Commission.\n\nSpecialties: Functional linguistics\nPostgraduate training and supervision\nCurriculum development\nAssessment of grant applications",
