                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2018
                }
            },
            "description": "\"The Construction of Discourse as Verbal Interaction\" showcases new work on discourse analysis by big names in the field and promising early-career researchers. Arising from the latest in the series of IWoDA workshops in Santiago de Compostela, it provides novel insights into both the explicit and the implicit characteristics of discourse as used in verbal interaction. This, in general terms, is the challenging terrain into which the contributors to this volume have ventured. The book combines theoretical issues with a practical orientation, comparing languages, analysing different registers, studying the openings of Skype conversations, and much more besides; it will prove highly relevant for postgraduate and advanced practitioners of discourse analysis, interaction studies, semantics and pragmatics. It was edited together with Mar\u00eda de los \u00c1ngeles G\u00f3mez Gonz\u00e1lez and appeared in September 2018 with John Benjamins Publishing Company. The book is a major product of the project 'The construction of discourse as social interaction: Contrastive implications and applications'.",
